&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about improving the lives of people with mental health issues, learning disabilities or substance misuse?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for 3 dedicated and proactive nurses or registered practitioners to work as part of our Street Triage Team. The team currently work alongside TEWV Urgent Care Services and Durham Constabulary and will soon be working with the North East Ambulance Service (NEAS). The role will be aligned to the wider crisis services already provided by Tees, Esk and Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust within the Durham and Darlington locality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The team works in partnership with Durham Constabulary and will work with NEAS to identify people with mental health needs and provide them with appropriate support, guidance and treatment.. We are looking for practitioners who can promote a culture of evidence based practice and provide excellent, responsive person centred care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be an innovative, creative practitioner with a desire to develop yourself but also able to contribute to the ongoing development of the services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you training and development, access to a number of opportunities and beneficial terms and conditions of employment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colin Docherty, Team Manager/ Advanced Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;colin.docherty@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07766473756&lt;/p&gt;
